article.headline: South Carolina 88, Longwood 58
article.story: COLUMBIA, S.C. -- Devan Downey scored 18 points to help South Carolina defeat Longwood 88-58 on Tuesday night and snap a two-game losing streak. Downey scored 17 points in a first half in which the Gamecocks (9-5) pulled ahead by 23 points. The Lancers (3-13) weren't much of a threat the rest of the way in South Carolina's final nonconference game before the Southeastern Conference opener on Saturday. The Gamecocks led 15-12 with about 11 minutes remaining before going on a 14-2 run. Downey, Evaldas Baniulis and Brandis Raley-Ross each hit a 3-pointer during the run. After a couple of Lancers (3-13) baskets, South Carolina closed the half on a 16-5 spurt to build a 47-24 lead at halftime. Baniulis added 15 points to break out of a season-long shooting slump. He came in shooting 25.5 percent from the field and 26 percent from beyond the arc, but finished 5-for-8 on 3-pointers.
